**HTML APIs are built-in browser interfaces that let developers interact with features like storage, multimedia, graphics, and device capabilities directly from JavaScript, making web pages more powerful and interactive.**  

---

## 🔑 What is an HTML API?
- **API (Application Programming Interface)**: A set of methods and properties that allow developers to interact with browser features.  
- **HTML APIs**: Introduced with HTML5, they extend the capabilities of web pages without requiring external plugins.  
- **Usage**: Always accessed via JavaScript, not directly through HTML tags.  

---

## 📘 Commonly Used HTML APIs

| **API** | **Purpose** | **Example Use Case** |
|---------|-------------|-----------------------|
| **DOM API** | Manipulates HTML elements dynamically | Change text, add/remove elements |
| **Canvas API** | Draw graphics, animations | Games, charts, image editing |
| **Geolocation API** | Access user’s location | Maps, delivery tracking |
| **Web Storage API** | Store data locally (persistent or session) | Save user preferences |
| **Fetch API** | Make network requests | Load data from servers |
| **Media API** | Control audio/video playback | Custom video players |
| **History API** | Manage browser history | Single-page applications (SPAs) |
| **Drag and Drop API** | Enable drag-and-drop functionality | File uploads, UI interactions |
| **Notifications API** | Show system notifications | Alerts, reminders |
| **Web Workers API** | Run scripts in background threads | Heavy computations without blocking UI |

